$interpreted: Dagger: Has the princess from the Kingdom of the Sun arrived yet?
Furygrowl: If she'd arrived, we'd have already seen her. We'll wait longer.
Dagger: Grrrrrr.
Dagger: Has the princess from the Kingdom of the Sun ARRIVED YET!?
Furygrowl: Why you asking again!?
Dagger: I'm no escort. Why'd they insist on putting ME in charge?
Furygrowl: Hah. Perhaps Chieftain Crushfang is testing your patience.

Dagger: Don't even mention him. Can you believe he
agreed to meet the princess for a peace treaty!
Dagger: We don't even know her. Aren't you feeling suspicious about it?
Furygrowl: Chieftain Crushfang is wise. He must have his reasons.
Dagger: Hmph. Humans are not worthy of trust, especially those from the Kingdom of the Sun...
Dagger: What, is the princess finally here?
Dumb Bear Soldier: Er, no~ I found tracks at the North West entrance. Not sure if they belong to trespassing miners...
Dagger: Do you even need to ask?! Won't take them long to reach nearest mining area.
Dumb Bear Soldier: What we do now? Tell Chieftain Crushfang?
Dagger: No need. I'm bored to death, let me teach them a lesson!
Furygrowl: Hey, how about the mission of escorting the princess?
Dagger: New guy, switch positions!
Skillful Illegal Miner: Finally found it.
Skillful Illegal Miner: QUICK. Once we collect enough, we get the hell out of here!
Dagger: In your dreams, shameless thieves!
Crushfang: ...Are treats prepared for the meeting? Remember, we need something humans can eat.
Old Priest: Do not worry, it's all prepared... we won't let them have any reason to say Bears have no manners...
Dagger: Chieftain Crushfang!
Dagger: Miners have entered from the North West entrance once more! I told you we need more warriors on guard there,
Dagger: yet you REFUSE to act!
Crushfang: Really? Where are they now?
Dagger: Beaten within an inch of their lives, locked away in a dungeon.
Crushfang: After the meeting with princess is over, we'll hand them over to Dylan.
Dagger: To that human, AGAIN?
Dagger: I don't know why you trust him.
Crushfang: To avoid trouble. The princess will visit our tribe soon.
Crushfang: No fighting is to happen here.
Dagger: Princess this, princess that...
Crushfang: Hold your horses. I sent you to escort the princess. How did you find trespassing miners?
Dagger: Um, well uh... I...
Crushfang: You had one job. What kind of Bear are you?!
Dagger: FINE. From now I'll follow the princess like a shadow.
Dagger: That good enough for you?
Old Priest: Still impulsive. Your expectations for him are too high.
Crushfang: Perhaps, but I'm sure one day he will change...
